    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hi Friends üëã, Welcome To aGuideHub!  To make mui backdrop background blur in react js, you can set and  to . it will make mui backdrop background blur in React‚Ä¶","html":"<p>Hi Friends üëã,</p>\n<p>Welcome To aGuideHub! </p>\n<p>To make mui backdrop background blur in react js, you can set <code class=\"language-text\">background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);</code>and <code class=\"language-text\">backdrop-filter: blur(5px);</code> to <code class=\"language-text\">MuiBackdrop-root</code>. it will make mui backdrop background blur in React JS.</p>\n<p>Today, I am going to show you, How to make mui backdrop background blur in react js</p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<p>Install the following packages to use mui backdrop in react js.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">npm</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npm install @mui<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>material @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>react @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>styled</code></pre></div>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">yarn</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">yarn add @mui<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>material @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>react @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>styled</code></pre></div>\n<p>Table of contents</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Install MUI and create a new React app.</li>\n<li>Import Material-UI backdrop.</li>\n<li>Use the backdrop Component</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Step 1: Install MUI and create a new React app.</h3>\n<p>First you have to install the React project. You should use <code class=\"language-text\">create-react-app</code> command to create a new React project.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npx create<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>react<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\ncd my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\nnpm start</code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 2: Import Material-UI backdrop.</h3>\n<p>After installing <code class=\"language-text\">MUI</code>, you have to import your React component. To do this, add the following line to the top of your component file.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token operator\">*</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">as</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> Backdrop <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"@mui/material/Backdrop\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> CircularProgress <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"@mui/material/CircularProgress\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> Button <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"@mui/material/Button\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"./styles.css\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 3: Use the backdrop Component.</h3>\n<p>The Backdrop signals a state change within the application and can be used for creating loaders, dialogs, and more. In its simplest form, the Backdrop component will add a dimmed layer over your application.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Backdrop\n  sx<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> <span class=\"token literal-property property\">color</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"#fff\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">zIndex</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">theme</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> theme<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>zIndex<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>drawer <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  open<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>open<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  onClick<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>handleClose<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>CircularProgress color<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"inherit\"</span> <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>Backdrop<span class=\"token operator\">></span>  </code></pre></div>\n<h2>MUI material make mui backdrop background blur example.</h2>\n<p>The below code is an example, you need to import <code class=\"language-text\">Backdrop</code> Component. Then, you can create a backdrop and you can use <code class=\"language-text\">background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);</code>and <code class=\"language-text\">backdrop-filter: blur(5px);</code>. Then it will make mui backdrop background blur in react js.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.js</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token operator\">*</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">as</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> Backdrop <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"@mui/material/Backdrop\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> CircularProgress <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"@mui/material/CircularProgress\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> Button <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"@mui/material/Button\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"./styles.css\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">SimpleBackdrop</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>open<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> setOpen<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> React<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">useState</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token boolean\">false</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">handleClose</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">setOpen</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token boolean\">false</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">handleOpen</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token function\">setOpen</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token boolean\">true</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Button onClick<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>handleOpen<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>Show backdrop<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>Button<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Backdrop\n        sx<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> <span class=\"token literal-property property\">color</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"#fff\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">zIndex</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">theme</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> theme<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>zIndex<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>drawer <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n        open<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>open<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n        onClick<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>handleClose<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>CircularProgress color<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"inherit\"</span> <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>Backdrop<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.css</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">.MuiBackdrop-root</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">background-color</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token function\">rgba</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>0<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> 0<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> 0<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> 0.5<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">backdrop-filter</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token function\">blur</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>5px<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>In the above code example, I have used the <code class=\"language-text\">@mui/material</code> component and made mui backdrop background blur in react js.</p>\n<p>Check the output of the above code example.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/025fec386e329279bd25aea7c43a9614/66be3/backdrop-background-blur.webp\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 50.632911392405056%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/webp;base64,UklGRkQAAABXRUJQVlA4IDgAAADwAgCdASoUAAoAPtFcpkyoJSOiMAgBABoJaQAAlNMAAAD9LRNqEJZMzY0NIZWogEs39fyfPuAAAA=='); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"React, backdrop, background, blur\"\n        title=\"React, backdrop, background, blur\"\n        src=\"/static/025fec386e329279bd25aea7c43a9614/8aab1/backdrop-background-blur.webp\"\n        srcset=\"/static/025fec386e329279bd25aea7c43a9614/81b7c/backdrop-background-blur.webp 158w,\n/static/025fec386e329279bd25aea7c43a9614/6ea66/backdrop-background-blur.webp 315w,\n/static/025fec386e329279bd25aea7c43a9614/8aab1/backdrop-background-blur.webp 630w,\n/static/025fec386e329279bd25aea7c43a9614/a70f5/backdrop-background-blur.webp 945w,\n/static/025fec386e329279bd25aea7c43a9614/4ef06/backdrop-background-blur.webp 1260w,\n/static/025fec386e329279bd25aea7c43a9614/66be3/backdrop-background-blur.webp 1362w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Here, we are provided code sandbox links for the above program make mui backdrop background blur in react js. Then you can use whenever you want and do the changes as per your requirements.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://aguidehub.com/codesandbox/?code=little-breeze-8lc2gv\" rel=\"nofollow\"  target=\"_BLANK\" >Try it Yourself</a></p>\n<p>All the best üëç</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"How to make mui backdrop background blur in react js?","tags":["React"],"date":"September 13, 2023","description":"Example of make mui backdrop background blur in React js with step by step tutorial - aGuideHub","social_image":"media/template/reactjs.jpg"}},"prev":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to change background color of mui backdrop in react js?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2023-09-13-how-to-change-background-color-of-mui-backdrop-in-react-js/"}},"next":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to create mui dialog with textfield in react js?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2023-09-12-how-to-create-mui-dialog-with-textfield-in-react-js/"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/2023-09-13-how-to-make-mui-backdrop-background-blur-in-react-js/","prevSlug":"/blog/2023-09-13-how-to-change-background-color-of-mui-backdrop-in-react-js/","nextSlug":"/blog/2023-09-12-how-to-create-mui-dialog-with-textfield-in-react-js/"}},
